{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0035-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Transclusion",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1770600000000,
  "modified": 1775225086615,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Transclusion embeds content from one item inside another. In Active Text documents, transclusions are inline nodes that resolve to the referenced item's content at render time."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Inserting Transclusions"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "In the Active Text editor, type "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "@@"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to open the transclusion autocomplete. Select an item and optionally a field. The editor inserts a "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":transclusion"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " node into the AST."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "How Transclusions Work"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A transclusion is stored as a "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":transclusion"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " AST node:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":pre",
        {
          "s": "[:transclusion \"item-id\" \"field-name\" \"display-text\"]"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "At render time, the doc renderer calls "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "get-field"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " on the referenced item and field, then renders the result inline. If the referenced item changes, the transclusion re-renders automatically via the reactive pipeline."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Transclusion vs Computed Fields"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Transclusions and computed fields are two faces of the same mechanism — both ultimately call "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "get-field"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ":"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Mechanism"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Where"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "How"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": ":transclusion"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " node"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Inline in document body"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Doc renderer calls "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "get-field"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " at render time"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "content.computed"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Named field on item"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Hob formula evaluated lazily via "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "get-field"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A computed field whose formula is "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "(get-field @other-item :description)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " is semantically identical to a transclusion of that item's description. See "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          "c0c0c0c0-0075-0000-0000-000000000000"
        ],
        {
          "s": " for the full comparison."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Eval Blocks"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "For more complex transclusion scenarios — queries, aggregations, conditional rendering — use eval blocks. Type "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ">>>"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " in the doc editor to insert an eval block, then write Hob code:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":pre",
        {
          "s": "clojure"
        },
        {
          "s": "(def modules (sort-by :name (find-items {:type @kernel-module})))\n(for [m modules]\n  [:doc\n    [:h3 [:item-ref (:id m) (:name m)]]\n    [:p (extract-text (nth (:description (:content m)) 1))]])"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Eval blocks have full access to the Hob environment and return Active Text nodes that are rendered inline."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Item References"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Item references ("
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "@"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " autocomplete in the editor) are distinct from transclusions. An item reference creates a clickable link to another item. A transclusion embeds the referenced item's "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "content"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "."
        }
      ],
      [
